name: model type
comment: This general class includes the most common types of models classified based on the level of description of the nervous system.
definition: Representation of the different types of models.

name: model component
comment: This class is based on the assumption that models can represented as particular assemblies of components that can be either specific to the different level of description (cellular
definition: Thing
externalSourceURI: representation of the components used to build the different model types

name: model parameter
comment: This class contains general parameters (voltage
definition: ...) rather than more specific parameters such membrane voltage
hasComponent: representation of the different parameters used to constrains models. The parameter can be either constant or variable.

name: parameter value
comment: Instances of this class will further specify the general parameters described in the class "model parameters".
definition: representation of the values describing a particular parameter: name

name: cellular model
comment: The distinction between the different subclasses is based on the different "spiking mechanisms".
definition: representation of the different model type used to describe nerve cells

name: synapse model
definition: representation of the different types of models used to represent synapses

name: network model
definition: representation of the different model types used to represent neural networks

name: plasticity model
definition: represent the different model types existing to describe plasticity mechanisms

name: artificial neuron model
comment: This class can be further subdivided into binary neuron
is_a: McCullogh neurons and all variants of the artificial neuron models.
externalSourceURI: representation of the abstract models of biological neurons.

name: point process model
definition: represent the statistical point process models used to reproduce particular feature of real neuron spiking patterns.

name: spiking model
definition: representation of the models describing the properties of nerve cells
externalSourceURI: designed to accurately describe and predict biological processes. This is in contrast with artificial neurons.

name: biophysical model
definition: representation of the class of models with a detailed spiking mechanisms representing the interaction between the fast sodium and slow potassium channels. The earliest example of this class is the Hogdkin and Huxley model of spike generation in the loligo axon.

name: threshold-based model
definition: representation of the models which represent the spiking mechanism as the result of a threshold crossing. The earliest example is the Lapicque's model (1907).

name: simplified model
comment: This class could become a superclass called dynamical models or dynamical system models in contrast with biophysical and threshold based models.
definition: representation of the models derived from Hodgkin and Huxley

name: detailed model
definition: represent models that have detailed spiking mechanism similar to Hodgkin and Huxley

name: conductance-based model
comment: Give a better definition. The problem is how to represent integrate and fire models with multiple conductances such as in Hill

name: one variable model
comment: find better definition?
definition: representation of the models including only one variable to describe the nerve cells behavior

name: two variable model
definition: representation of the models that include two variables to describe the nerve cells behavior

name: three variable models
definition: representation of the models that include three variables to describe the nerve cells behavior

name: spike response model
definition: representation of the models that correspond to a generalization of the leaky integrate-and-fire model and give a simple description of action potential generation in neurons

name: current-based model
comment: This particularity is created by keeping the postsynaptic membrane voltage constant in the current equation => isyn=gsyn*(Cte-Erev)

name: conductance-based model
comment: In this case
is_a: the postsynaptic membrane potential is varying over time. It allows to capture phenomenon such as shunting inhibition

name: artificial neural network model
comment: corresponds to Kohonen maps
synonym: represent the abstract neural network models based on artificial neuron models

name: cellular plasticity
comment: This class would contains models that describes the link between potassium channels and NMDA activation as described in hippocampus for instance.
definition: represent the models that describe variations of the cellular intrinsic excitability due to activity.

name: cellular model component
definition: representation the different elements used to build cellular model types

name: resting membrane potential
comment: Big question: Should it be considered as a parameter rather than a component?
definition: membrane potential at rest

name: refractory period
comment: Could be considered as parameter?
definition: represents the amount of time it takes for an excitable membrane to be ready for a second stimulus once it returns to its resting state following excitation

name: model quality
definition: represents a qualitative feature of the model that can be either independent of the model specification or a property resulting of the particular model specification

name: spiking mechanism
definition: represents the mechanisms generating action potential in nerve cells in model

name: morphology
definition: represents the models of nerve cell morphology

name: intracellular dynamic
definition: represents models of chemical signaling occuring inside the nerve cell

name: stimulation current
definition: represents models describing input currents provided to the model via an electrode (intracellular or extracellular).

name: ionic current
definition: represents the models describing the flow of current through uniquely voltage-gated channels

name: synaptic current
definition: represents the models describing the flow of current through chemically-gated channels or gap junctions (connexons).

name: abstract current
definition: represents the models of currents reproducing a particular cellular behavior such as rebound or adaptation.

name: continuous
definition: represents the models considering the action potential initiation as a continuous process
externalSourceURI: to be considered in contrast with threshold-based mechanisms.

name: threshold-based
definition: represents the models considering the action potential initiation as a result of a thresholding opearion
externalSourceURI: to be considered in contrast with continuous mechanisms.

name: point
definition: represents the models without specified morphology

name: single compartment
definition: represents models with one compartment

name: multiple compartment
definition: represents the models with an abstract morphology with multiple compartments as the Ball-and-stick model

name: reconstructed
comment: Could a quality of the model rather than a component. Reference to the definition of quality by BFO
definition: represents models with morphology build upon the reconstruction of a real nerve cell morphology using imaging techniques such as camera lucida or two-photon imaging.

name: calcium dynamic
definition: represents models describing the dynamic of the intracellular calcium concentration over time.

name: biochemical dynamic
definition: represents models describing the dynamic of the intracellular biochemical reactions and molecular participant concentrations over time.

name: non linear spike generation current
definition: represents an additional non-linear current ψ which leads to

spiking current
comment: related to HindMarch and Rose model

name: bursting current
comment: related to HindMarch and Rose model. see Wikipedia for definition.

name: membrane recovery mechanism
comment: As a reference of variable u in Izhikevich model.

name: cellular elements
comment: Should be linked to the cellular models with an object property such as "isInstanceOf"
definition: representation of the cellular element model used to build the network model

name: synaptic element
comment: Should be linked to the "synaptic models" with object property as for cellular element
definition: representation of the synaptic elements used to build a network model

name: connectivity pattern
comment: should be linked with connectivity rule
definition: represents well-defined categories of connectivity patterns obtained with specific connectivity rules

name: current type
definition: represents the different types of currents that can influence the trajectory of the membrane voltage

name: current localization
definition: represents the location of the current source on a neuronal model (somatic

name: current distribution
definition: represents the spatial distribution of current sources (ionic channels

name: spatial embedding
comment: Models can be defined without any mention of space.

comment: relates to http://neurolex.org/wiki/Category:Two_dimensional_region

name: three dimensional layout
comment: http://neurolex.org/wiki/Category:Three_dimensional_region

comment: model of network plasticity based on developmental rules that will change the structure of the network: Van Ooyen

name: morphological quality
comment: Similar to sao1057800815

name: functional quality

definition: synchronization
